title: For Sale:  WWII GERMAN ZF4 G43 SNIPER SCOPE Complete w/ Original Mount & Matching Case.
postcontent: Here's a great item for the WWII colletor! This is an original ZF4 sniper scope for the German G.43 semi-automatic rifle. This scope is complete with the original (non-repro) mount, rainshield, lens covers, rubber eye protector, packet of lens cloth, and even the original wood scope case with strap! The scope is maker coded "dow" for Opticotechna GmbH in Czechoslovakia and the serial number (3200) indicates fairly early production. The triangle filled with blue paint indicates the scope was manufactured for cold weather use (Russia, Norway, etc). The mount was manufactured by Berliner-Lubecker (E/214 marked) and is of the early type with "center bend" lever and square base ends. The mount is serial numbered to its rifle (6570) the correct pantagraph engraved/block style numerals marked through the dark phosphate finish. The rainshield is of the standard type with blue finish and three grasping legs. The lens cover is correct with pressed paper "Presstoff" cap construction with leather strap and wooden plug that fits into the rubber eye protector. The case is of the later wood style construction and is correct, original and matching. It is stencil numbered and matched to the rifle with the same 6570 engraved on the mount. The case is Army accepted with an ink stamped Eagle/WaA217 inside the lid, as is correct. Likewise, the case closing hardware is stamped with the "triangle within a circle" marking, another good indicator of originality. There is a place to store the rainshield inside the lid and a slot inside the body which holds a pair of lens filters. A note about the lens filters: these are not originals but were hand made by a famous master Optometrist. The original filters were simply held in place by the rubber eye protector and were designed to both reduce brightness in bright daylight and to serve to protect the lens from dirt.Overall condition is very good.

title: For Sale:  Chainpure Khukuri imported from Nepal - FREE SHIPPING!!!
postcontent: The Chainpure Kukri comes with a very nicely carved Indian Rosewood sheath - but don't let that fool you, this blade is no sister Sally!!If you're looking for a gift for someone that's a little nicer than your average kukri but still has an awesome take-no-prisoners blade.....YOU'RE WELCOME.  Seriously, these make great gifts for knife lovers.  Not like those $75 "samurai" swords where the blade breaks off at the handle if you breath on it.  But I'm getting off topic so....Hailing from Chainpure, Nepal (well duh, I mean look at the name) this design is a little different than your traditional Khukuri.  Look at the pictures, they're worth, what, at least 50 words?  Something like that; my math may be off.The blade itself is 10" long set in a 5" Indian Rosewood handle.  What makes this one really stand out is the Indian Rosewood sheath that's hand carved and brass bound.  It really is a work of art.Kadra and Chakmak are included (utility knife and sharpener).There is a brass belt look on the back of the sheath.These blades are all HAND CRAFTED!  While the Kami adhere to set standards when making these each one will have slight variances and unique qualities to it.The blades are made from high grade carbon steel, often sourced from old railway lines or truck/jeep springs.  Legend has it that the blades are indesctructible; not hard to see why.From the most utilitarian design to the most ornately guilded works of art, all Khukuri are fully functional and built to last.FEEL FREE TO ASK ANY QUESTIONS.  I WILL ENTERTAIN OFFERS.Shipping is FREE to lower 48 states.  Alaska and Hawaii will incur an additional $5 shipping charge.  No international shipping is offered at this time.RETURNS:  Please inspect the knife immediatly upon arrival.  If there is a functional issue or the knife is damaged upon arrival we will accept a return for refund.  We will not accept returns on knives that have been used or mistreated.  You will be responsible for shipping the item back to us.  Return must be well packaged and shipped insured.
